{%- assign sid = section.id -%}

{%- style -%}
#nx-usage-{{ sid }} {
  max-width: var(--container-width-narrow);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 8px 16px;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, sans-serif);
  color: var(--color-text-main, #111827);
  line-height: 1.7;
  content-visibility: auto;
}
#nx-usage-{{ sid }} h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-heading-family, sans-serif);
  font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin: 0 0 12px;
}
#nx-usage-{{ sid }} ul { padding-left: 18px; margin: 0; }
#nx-usage-{{ sid }} li {
  margin: 8px 0;
  color: var(--color-text-muted, #4b5563);
}
#nx-usage-{{ sid }} li strong { color: var(--color-text-main, #111827); }
{%- endstyle -%}

<section id="nx-usage-{{ sid }}" aria-label="Usage and cycling guidance">
  <h2>Timing, Usage &amp; Cycling</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Start low</strong> and adjust only if needed.</li>
    <li><strong>With food?</strong> Fat-soluble: Aniracetam, Pramiracetam. Water-soluble: Fasoracetam (Phenylpiracetam Hydrazide varies by individual).</li>
    <li><strong>Targeted use:</strong> Many prefer as-needed for study blocks, presentations, or deep work.</li>
    <li><strong>Periodic breaks:</strong> Brief breaks help compare baseline vs benefit.</li>
    <li><strong>Choline tightness/head fog?</strong> Consider adding a choline donor and reassess.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

{% schema %}
{ "name": "NX — Usage & Cycling", "settings": [], "presets": [{ "name": "NX — Usage & Cycling" }] }
{% endschema %}
